doc.after: A dictionary is a collection of words in one or more specific languages, often listed alphabetically (or by radical and stroke for ideographic languages), with usage of information, definitions, etymologies, phonetics, pronunciations, translation, and other information;[1] or a book of words in one language with their equivalents in another, also known as a lexicon.[1] It is a lexicographical product designed for utility and function, curated with selected data, presented in a way that shows inter-relationships among the data.[2]
